  <div id="guts">
    <h1>pirate</h1>

    <p>
        Pirate is a scala library that provides a mechanism for parsing
        command line arguments and producing usage strings.
    </p>


    <h2>quick start</h2>

    <p>
        Documentation is currently light on. The best place to start is
        the demos:
        <ul>
          <li> io.mth.pirate.demo.SwitchesDemo </li>
          <li> io.mth.pirate.demo.PositionalArgsDemo </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>release</h2>

    <p>
      There is not an official release yet. If you want to try it out, the source can be found at <a href="https://github.com/markhibberd/pirate">github</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>code</h2>

    <p>
      Grab the code from the mirror on <a href="https://github.com/markhibberd/pirate">github</a>. 
    </p>

    <h2>license</h2>

    <p>
     The code is free to use under the terms of a <a href="https://github.com/markhibberd/pirate/blob/master/LICENSE">3 point BSD license</a>


    </p>

    <h2>contact</h2>

    <p>
